              <floruit notBefore="1667" notAfter="1700">He was a member of the Gondarine court and the royal chronicler. 
                 He also belonged to the higher clergy in the court of Gondarine rulers. Intially,
                 he was the azzāž (official to administer court activities) in the court of King <persName ref="PRS10375Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs I</persName> and
                 towards the end of the reign of King <persName ref="PRS10375Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs I</persName> he was granted the title of <roleName type="title">ṣaḥāfe tǝʾǝzāz</roleName>. 
                 He was the author of <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3947ChronYohannes">Chronicle of Yohannǝs I</ref> and also partly the  
                 <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3950ChronIyasu">Chronicle of ʾIyāsu I</ref>.
                 
               </floruit>
               <death> He died in <date>04-05-1700</date>. He was killed in a battle between the royal army and the warriors of the
                  <persName ref="ETH1973Oromo"/><persName ref="ETH1604Guduru"/>.</death>
               
            </person>
